# Frontend Architecture

## Design Philosophy
- **Feature-based**: each domain owns its own components, hooks, services, and types
- **Dumb UI, Smart Hooks**: components render; hooks think; services fetch
- **Design system first**: never style ad-hoc — use Tailwind tokens from `tailwind.config.js`
- **No prop-drilling beyond 2 levels**: lift to context or server state (React Query)

## Folder Structure

```
src/
  app/              ← providers, router, App root (no feature logic here)
  features/
    documents/
      components/   ← presentational components for this feature
      hooks/        ← useDocuments, useUpload (data + state logic)
      services/     ← raw API calls (returns typed data)
      index.ts      ← barrel export
    chat/           ← same pattern
  components/
    ui/             ← design system: Button, Card, Input, Badge, Spinner…
    layout/         ← Sidebar, Header, Layout wrapper
  lib/
    api/            ← axios client + response interceptors
    utils/          ← pure utility functions
  pages/            ← thin shell: imports feature components, sets page title
  types/            ← app-level types that extend shared/
```

## Component Rules

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — single responsibility, typed props, no business logic
interface DocumentCardProps {
  document: Document;
  onDelete: (id: string) => void;
}
export function DocumentCard({ document, onDelete }: DocumentCardProps) { ... }

// ❌ BAD — fetching inside a presentational component
export function DocumentCard({ id }: { id: string }) {
  const [doc, setDoc] = useState();
  useEffect(() => { fetch(`/api/documents/${id}`)... }, [id]);
}
```

## Custom Hooks Rules
- One hook per concern; hooks can call other hooks
- Hooks own loading/error state; expose clean interface
- Prefix: `use<Noun>` for data hooks, `use<Verb>` for action hooks

```typescript
// ✅ data hook
export function useDocuments() {
  return useQuery({ queryKey: ['documents'], queryFn: documentsService.list });
}

// ✅ action hook
export function useUploadDocument() {
  const queryClient = useQueryClient();
  return useMutation({
    mutationFn: documentsService.upload,
    onSuccess: () => queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['documents'] }),
  });
}
```

## Service Layer (API calls)

```typescript
// features/documents/services/documents.service.ts
// Returns typed data — never ApiResponse envelope
export const documentsService = {
  list: (): Promise<Document[]> =>
    apiClient.get<ApiResponse<Document[]>>('/documents').then(r => r.data.data),
  upload: (file: File): Promise<Document> => { ... },
};
```

## State Management
- **Server state**: React Query (useQuery / useMutation) — never useState for remote data
- **UI state**: useState / useReducer in the component or hook
- **Global UI state** (modals, theme): React Context, scoped to `app/`
- No Redux unless the team explicitly decides otherwise

## UI Design Tokens (Tailwind)
Use the design scale consistently:
- Spacing: `4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48` (px-1 = 4px)
- Radius: `rounded-lg` (8px) for cards/inputs, `rounded-full` for chips/avatars
- Brand color: `brand-600` primary, `brand-50` backgrounds, `brand-700` hover
- Shadows: `shadow-sm` on cards, `shadow-md` on modals
- Typography: `text-sm` (14px) body, `text-base` (16px) prose, `text-2xl font-bold` page headings

## Error & Loading States
Every data-dependent component must handle all three states:
```tsx
if (isLoading) return <Spinner />;
if (isError) return <ErrorMessage error={error} />;
return <ActualContent data={data} />;
```

## File Size Limits
- Component file: ≤ 150 lines — extract sub-components if exceeded
- Hook file: ≤ 80 lines
- Service file: ≤ 60 lines
